{
  "texts": [
    "Visualization: ggplot2 library is used for data visualization to show the distribution of fraudulent and nonfraudulent transactions in the new feature space.",
    "Fraudulent and non-fraudulent transactions are distinguished by different colors and shapes so that they have a clear distinction in the new feature space, which helps in subsequent modeling and analysis.",
    "Class ImbalanceAs stated before, the fraud and non-fraud cases available in the present dataset have extremely imbalanced weights, with only 1.2% out of the total cases being fraud.",
    "[10][11][12]Therefore, there are only 7,000 observations labeled as fraud, while the rest 580,000 observations are labeled as clean transactions.",
    "In a classification problem, this would create difficulties for a model to correctly identify the fraud label, because it is so scarce throughout the dataset.This data structure issue can be solved by using two different sampling techniques: undersampling or oversampling."
  ]
}